    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Horn</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Horn</title>
        <table id="t0827205" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Horn</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.55in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.94in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.84in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.40in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At 15A fuse F5-C and circuit 14AM, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>F5-C, 14AM to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 14AM or 14K from battery stud (B1), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Remove horn relay (463-R7) and at circuit 85, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(463)/R7, 85 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 85 or 15A fuse F5-C, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (463-R7) circuit 85A, measure voltage to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(463)/R7, 85A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 85A, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At relay socket (463-R7) circuit 85C, measure resistance to ground while an assistant
                                depresses the horn button.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(463)/R7, 85C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60; 1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 85C, conn. (N/L), circuit 85A, conn. (N/L),
                                black wire, conn. (N/L), black wire, slip ring, black wire, or horn button to chassis
                                ground, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Re-install horn relay (463-R7). Disconnect connector (214), and at circuit 85B,
                                measure voltage to ground while an assistant depresses the horn button.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(214), 85B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 85B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>At horn connector (214), measure voltage from circuit 85B to 85-G while an assistant
                                depresses the horn button.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>(214), 85B to 85-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 85-G or 11-GI, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Reconnect connector (214). Horn circuits check good. If horn fails to sound, replace
                                horn.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
